===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|sweren}}, {{m|enm|swerien}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|swerian||to swear, take an oath of office}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*swarjaną||to speak, swear}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*swer-||to speak, talk}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|swarre||to swear}}, {{cog|stq|swera||to swear}}, {{cog|nl|zweren||to swear, vow}}, {{cog|nds|swören||to swear}}, {{m|nds|sweren}}, {{cog|de|schwören||to swear}}, {{cog|da|sværge}}, {{cog|sv|svära||to swear}}, {{cog|is|sverja||to swear}}. Also cognate to {{cog|sq|var||to hang, consider, to depend from}} through Proto-Indo-European.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|swears|swearing|swore|sworn}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive|transitive}} To take an [[oath]].
